
First of all download from Mono subversion repository Mono.Cecil 
(http://anonsvn.mono-project.com/viewcvs/trunk/mcs/class/Mono.Cecil.tar.gz?view=tar)
and uncompress it in the directory tools

  ( cd tools ; tar xzvf .../Mono.Cecil.tar.gz )

create a directory where to build, enter it and configure

  mkdir builddir
  cd builddir
  .../configure --target=cil32 --with-ilasm=<.../ilasm> --prefix=<installdir>

for the moment use ilasm from pnet (DotGNU),
the one from Mono has a bug compiling varargs function calls (Bug 364580)

now just build and install it

  make
  make install
